snippet: After routing the Congolese M23 rebels, United Nations peacekeepers are expected to turn their attention to subduing a Hutu militia.
abstract: United Nations peacekeepers, having helped rout powerful rebel group M23 in eastern Democratic Republic of Congo, are expected to take on ethnic Hutu militia known as Democratic Forces for the Liberation of Rwanda, or FDLR, whose members Rwanda holds responsible for the 1994 genocide.
lead_paragraph: After routing the Congolese M23 rebels, United Nations peacekeepers are expected to turn their attention to subduing a Hutu militia.
